    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-05-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-05-13T15:40:37Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Personal Philanthropy Account Act of 2006 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax deduction (whether or not the taxpayer itemizes deductions) for cash contributions to a personal philanthropy account. Defines &quot;personal philanthropy account&quot; as a tax-exempt trust created to make distributions for charitable purposes. Sets forth rules providing for default charitable distributions in the event of an account holder's death and minimum annual distribution requirements.</p><p>Allows an exclusion from the gross income of an employee for contributions made by an employer to the employee's personal philanthropy account. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
